CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Barbed-Wire Barricade - Some of the barbed wire, which Ross Christopher strung across the driveway entrance to the Alonzo Sanders' property and which Sanders was forced to cut on more than one occasion in order to get in and out of his tract of land, is wrapped around this tree. Christopher claims several feet of his land is included in Sanders' property. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Barbed wire tangled next to large tree at the side of Alonzo R. Sanders' driveway entrance, Eighty Four Pennsylvania
